  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are currently selling delta into this move as SPX trades just below the massive 6580 gamma wall (64.5B), creating strong resistance that should cap upside momentum in this PIN regime. The thick positive gamma concentration between 6575-6590 acts as a magnet pulling price back toward this range, while the wall break and GEX surge events suggest dealers just absorbed significant gamma flow requiring immediate delta hedging. \n\nWatch 6580 as the critical flip level - any sustained break above triggers dealer buying that could accelerate the move to 6585-6590, but failure here should see mean reversion back toward the 6570 support wall where dealers turn into buyers.",
